parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spontaneous shattering of the rear windshield/liftgate glass can cause safety hazards, distractions, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear windshield/liftgate glass shatters without any apparent cause

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration and fluttering of the hood can cause distractions, glare, and potential accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The hood vibrates or flutters at speeds above 30-40 mph
causing sunlight to flicker into the driver's field of vision
and creating a distracting and potentially hazardous situation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poorly designed hood support rod can cause burns or injuries when touched, especially after driving.
symptoms: The hood support rod becomes extremely hot after driving
causing burns or injuries when touched.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cabin Boom Noise and Suspension Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cabin boom noise and suspension issues can cause physical illness, including ear pain, headaches, nausea, and disorientation, which can be a significant safety concern while driving. The noise can also be distracting and affect the driver's ability to focus on the road.
symptoms: Low-frequency bass noise (below 30Hz) reverberating throughout the entire vehicle
and disorientation; cabin pressure; deep bass sound; ear pressure; vibrations in the cabin; popping or clicking noises when turning or accelerating; wobbling front wheel.
